results.name: Difference between n and the result obtained when n is remultiplied from N to GF(2)[X]: a(n) = n - A234741(n).
comment: a(n) is the difference of n and the number obtained when the prime divisors of n are multiplied together in such a way that the carry-bits from intermediate products are discarded, as in A048720.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..8191
xref: Cf. A235034 (gives the positions of zeros).
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Jan 24 2014
